parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption can lead to engine failure, which can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle consumes excessive amounts of oil
even after regular oil changes. This can lead to engine failure

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, putting the safety of the driver and passengers at risk.
symptoms: often due to excessive oil consumption
resulting in costly repairs or replacement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Intake manifold issues can cause engine stalling, loss of control, and accidents.
Transmission failure can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: causing the vehicle to jerk or die.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause accidents or leave the driver stranded, putting the safety of the driver and passengers at risk.
symptoms: especially at slow speeds or when making turns.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of control, accidents, or injuries, especially if the vehicle is unable to be stopped in time.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates independently when shifting from park into any other gear without warning
resulting in increased RPMs and requiring force to be applied to the brake pedal to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission/transfer case failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or stranding the driver.
symptoms: often without warning; clunking noises from the transmission when shifting into reverse or drive; clunking noises when coming to a stop while driving; and jolting sensations.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to diagnose and repair drivetrain issues can lead to continued vehicle problems, safety risks, and financial burdens for the owner.
symptoms: Dealerships and independent mechanics may fail to diagnose or repair drivetrain issues
such as transmission and transfer case problems
despite the owner's reports of symptoms and requests for assistance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and damage to the vehicle, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: the tread separates from the tire
